      • autoCast

        public static Object autoCast(Object o)
        BPlusTree is able to manage comparable objects or tuples. If tuples are used (wrapped by Entry class) the Object o is a tuple (non-comparable) or a tuple subset which is the key (and have to be comparable). In order to manage this casting (for delegation to BPlusTree) use this method which automatically cast o to fit the requirements.
        Parameters:
        o - Object, e.g. primitive or tuple (or tuple subset)
        Returns:
        The matching object

      • toInt

        public static int toInt(RelationalType relationalType)
        Converts a object of RelationalType to SQL Type which is an integer.

        Example 
                        int sqlType = Convert.toInt(RelationalType.ARRAY); // sqlTyp is now equal to java.sql.Types.ARRAY (= 2003)
        Parameters:
        relationalType - An object of type RelationalType which covers SQL types as an enum
        Returns:
        The SQL Type value of relationalType or java.sql.Types.OTHER if it fails
        See Also:
        RelationalType, Types

      • toJavaType

        public static JavaType toJavaType(RelationalType relationalType)
        Converts RelationalType object into JavaType type.
        For type converting, see JDBC Types and IBM: Data types that map to database data types in Java applications
        Parameters:
        relationalType - Your object of type RelationalType which should be converted
        Returns:
        The assigned java type or JavaType.UNKNOWN if it fails.
        See Also:
        RelationalType, JavaType

      • toRelationalType

        public static RelationalType toRelationalType(int sqlTypConstant)
        Converts a object of SQL Type which is an integer to RelationalType.

        Example 
                        RelationalType relType = Convert.toRelationalType(java.sql.ARRAY); // relType is now equal to RelationalType.ARRAY
        Parameters:
        sqlTypConstant - An value of SQL Type
        Returns:
        The RelationalType value of sqlTypConstant or RelationalType.OTHER if it fails
        See Also:
        RelationalType, JavaType

      • getFiber

        public Integer[] getFiber(RelationalType e)
        Returns the fiber of toRelationalType(int) at e, that means the inverse image (preimage) of the singleton e. In other words this method returns all Integers i for which #toRelationalType(i) equals e holds.
        Parameters:
        e - a relational type
        Returns:
        the preimage of e
